snippet.textDisplay: I don't know why... but YouTube gave me a referral that lead me here :) and I am just grinning... I had a '94 burgundy Plymouth Voyager LE (and I had to unfortunately give it up back to my parents so they could sell it for $200 because the windshield cracked...) but I was absolutely goofy enough to put a stereo configured 5k Watt sub system in the back with a Jenson 160 Watt flip display topped off with music reactive lighting effects. (yup... high school...) It had the 3.3L V6 engine and wow did it take off making ricers jaws drop, crazy stock engine, head gasket had to be replaced twice, same with the transition and alternators (hmm, i wonder why :D )
